      notes: "No prescription exclusion list in the Silver Guard agent guide. The guide states applications are underwritten via INSpeed or paper application with Part I and Part II health questions only.; NOT a definitive knockout list. The decision engine evaluates prescription history holistically: prescription type, dosage, frequency of fills, date of last fill, prescribing doctor specialty, and applicant age/gender are all factors. Example: 1 low-dose fill of Oxycodone from a Dentist is viewed differently than 45 fills of high dosage from an Oncologist. These medications are 'significantly likely to result in a decline if currently taken or recently present.'; Agent guide references 'cross reference any prescriptions taken by the applicant against the prescription drug list' during pre-qualification, but the prescription drug list was not included in the source documents. Pharmacy records database check is part of routine underwriting.; No prescription exclusion list in the Generation Legacy agent guide. Underwriting includes a medical history database check and point-of-sale telephone interview.; Not documented in consumer brochure.; Not documented in consumer brochure.",
